<1ST_LINE>r i PM-NewGuineaQuake     11-14 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-New Guinea Quake,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Strong Quake Recorded Near Papua New Guinea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake was recorded today in the
Bismarck archipelago northeast of Papua New Guinea, the Hong Kong
observatory reported.
   The observatory said the quake struck at 10:24 a.m. (9:24 p.m.
Sunday EST) and registered a preliminary magnitude of 6.7 on the
open-ended Richter scale.
   The earthquake's epicenter was about 530 miles north northeast of
Port Moresby in Papua New Guinea, the observatory said. It had no
further details about the quake.
   The Richter scale measures the total strength of an earthquake as
recorded on seismographs. Every increase of one number represents a
tenfold increase in magnitude. An earthquake measuring six on the
scale is capable of causing extensive damage in populated areas.
</TEXT>
