<HEAD>Five People Killed in Plane Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HELSINKI, Finland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A turboprop plane of the domestic
airline Wasawings crashed today in western Finland, killing at least
five people, state radio said.
   The radio quoted airline officials as saying the EMB-110 P1
Bandeirante aircraft was carrying 10 passengers and two pilots on a
routine domestic flight of 210 miles from Helsinki to Seinajoki.
Both pilots were among those killed.
   The cause of the crash was not known immediately.
   It was the worst air accident in Finland in at least a decade.
