<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Border guards fought a gun battle with
Colombian bandits who planned to kidnap a rancher and captured three
of them, a national guard officer said Monday.
   The Saturday shootout near the town of Casigua, about 300 miles
west of Caracas, stopped the Colombians from kidnapping the rancher,
Nolberto Guttierez, said Gen. Vinicio Barrios Puche.
