<HEAD>Man Says He Tried to Smother Wife, She Fought Him Off</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST HAMPTON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 84-year-old man was released without
bail after allegedly trying to smother his wife in a mercy-killing
attempt that failed when she woke up and fought him off, officials
said.
   Town Justice Edward Horne said he released George Wootan without
bail on Sunday on the recommendation of the Suffolk County district
attorney's office.
   Wootan is charged with the attempted murder of his 76-year-old
wife, Olivia, to whom he has been married more than 50 years.
   He told police his wife was in pain and could only sleep after
taking sleeping pills, Horne said Monday. Wootan said he put a
pillow over her on Saturday, but she woke up and thwarted him,
according to Horne.
   Wootan then called police and turned himself in, Horne said.
   Horne said his main concern in releasing Wootan was that he
remain away from his wife until the case is settled. Mrs. Wootan was
in the hospital at the time of the court hearing and has since gone
to stay with a son in upstate New York, he said.
   The justice said that until he learns the woman's wishes, he will
not let them live together. She may decide she does not want to
prosecute, Horne said.
   Horne scheduled a hearing Thursday, when he expects the district
attorney's office to tell him whether it plans to prosecute.
</TEXT>
