<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Retail     11-14 0259</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Retail,0270</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>K mart Reports Third-Quarter Earnings Surge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TROY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   K mart Corp. reported Monday its third-quarter
earnings rose 14.6 percent as the retailer's sales increased 6.4
percent.
   K mart reported income of $126.1 million, or 63 cents a share,
for the 13 weeks ended Oct. 28, up from $110.1 million, or 54 cents
a share, in the same period in 1987.
   The company said sales for the period rose to $6.36 billion from
$5.97 billion in the third quarter of last year.
   On a comparable store basis _ based on stores open in the third
quarter both this year and last _ sales were up 2.4 percent, K mart
said.
   Joseph E. Antonini, K mart chairman and chief executive officer,
said sales rose at a faster rate in the third quarter than the first
or second.
   ``This suggests that customers are responding to our lowering of
shelf prices, our strengthened once-a-week advertising program and
to our various merchandising programs,'' Antonini said.
   Antonini said 1,113 K mart stores were linked with the company's
point-of-sale computerized central inventory control system, up from
729 a year earlier.
   For the first nine months of its fiscal year, K mart said it had
income of $409.7 million, or $2.04 a share, on sales of $18.88
billion, up from $371 million, or $1.82 a share, on sales of $17.87
billion in the nine months ended Oct. 26, 1987.
   The company had 2,243 K mart discount stores, 1,213 Waldenbooks,
133 Builders Square and 257 Pay Less Drug stores as of Oct. 26.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
