<1ST_LINE>r f AM-IBM-Networks     11-14 0112</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-IBM-Networks,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>IBM Announces Faster Network Products</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   International Business Machines Corp. on Monday
announced products that allow a network to handle 16 million bits of
information per second, four times the previous speed.
   IBM said the improvements in its Token-Ring network, which
competes with the industry-standard Ethernet and Digital Equipment
Corp.'s Decnet, ``gives customers the increased speed and
performance they need to engage in advanced graphics, image and
engineering and scientific applications.''
   The Token-Ring network can be used to link computers of all
sizes. The enhancements include a special signal converter chip that
does the work of six other chips and is made with state-of-the-art
fabrication technology.
</TEXT>
